Sonic Launches High-Yield Algorithmic Stablecoin, Evoking Memories of the Terra-Luna Crash

Sonic is launching a new yield-generating algorithmic stablecoin, bringing back memories of the Terra-Luna collapse in 2022. Despite concerns, Andre Cronje, co-founder of Sonic Labs, claims their model is solid, with proof-of-concept tests showing an APR of 200% at $10 million TVL, stabilizing around 4.9% at $1 billion.

Do you believe in the success of this project?

text:
Sonic Labs Tests High-Yield Stablecoin

Sonic Labs (formerly Fantom) is trialing a new algorithmic stablecoin, Minimal USD (MUSD), offering annual yields up to 23%.

Co-founder Andre Cronje ("Godfather of DeFi") revealed the interest rate will scale based on protocol TVL:
🔸200% yield at $10M TVL
🔸23.5% yield at $100M TVL
🔸~4.9% yield above $1B TVL
